{
  "stem": "10588.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that was later for pillows, for down quilts.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And always she used to say, [NON-ENGLISH], which means 'God willing'-- when Itkele-- I was the oldest, and I was the [? firstborn-- ?] she's going to get married, she's going to have nice, you know, pillows, with down and everything else.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And whenever they were making [INAUDIBLE], that was always their wish, and that's why I feel so horrible that they didn't live to fulfill that wish.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They should be able to take me under the chuppah, which means under the canopy, when I'm going to get married.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Ciechonw was a small town-- as I mentioned, 90 kilometer north of Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I looked out through the window, I saw in the morning little boys with payele, with the Hasidic, you know-- going to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "People were religious.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was-- it had a [NON-ENGLISH], which means a special-- where there were made loans.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Let's say, if somebody was poor and they needed a loan to go in business or to help somebody, people would lend money.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they would lend them to those.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But, in order not to shame them-- was a prohibition against shaming somebody.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was not menschlich.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they would know who they were loaning the money, and the other was-- it was anonymous, you know?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Charity giving was supposed to be anonymous.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Speaking of charity, when I was a little girl, I remember, every morning-- because the story of charity reminds me of something of the grandmother that I was planning to tell you.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Every morning, when I got up, my grandmother would say with me the prayers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[SPEAKING YIDDISH]-- you know, the prayer.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
